<item>
            <title>[JDK-8348936] [Accessibility,macOS,VoiceOver] VoiceOver doesn&apos;t announce untick on toggling the checkbox with &quot;space&quot; key on macOS</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8348936</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Test Type: Accessibility&lt;br/&gt;
Tested With: SwingSet2.jar&lt;br/&gt;
Products Tested: jdk-8u451 b02, jdk-11.0.27 b01, jdk-17.0.9 b09, jdk-21.0.7 b03, 24.0.1 b02, JDK 25 b07&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Steps to reproduce:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Run SwingSet2.jar&lt;br/&gt;
2. Go to checkbox demo&lt;br/&gt;
3. Turn on VoiceOver.&lt;br/&gt;
4. Navigate the focus on checkbox using tab key.&lt;br/&gt;
5. Press only &amp;quot;space&amp;quot; key: It will also tick or untick the checkbox, but VoiceOver announces the tick only, and it does NOT announce the untick.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Expectation: VoiceOver should announce both tick and untick.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Also tested the native macOS checkbox: on toggling the native checkbox using space key it announces both tick and untick, Java checkbox should also announce the same.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Note: Only with jdk-17.0.9 b09 it announces both tick and untick, for rest all the releases it announces tick only.</description>
